===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|ford}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*furduz}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*pértus||crossing}}. Cognate with English {{term|firth|lang=en}}, {{term|fjord|lang=en}} (via Old Norse), Low German {{m|nds|Föörd}}, Dutch {{m|nl|voord}}, German {{term|Furt|lang=de}}, Danish and Norwegian {{m|no|fjord}}, and more distantly with English {{term|port|lang=en}} (via Latin).

